Attended a Sunday Brunch at the Greenhouse Cafe for the first time. We have been searching for a decent brunch location around Bayridge for a while, and we thought that this location would be an amazing place considering their menu options, as well as their unlimited cocktails. We ordered the chicken, and steak sandwiches and they were both amazing. The food overall was above standard, but the service was a little rough. The location wasn’t busy until an hour after we have already been seated, however, during the slow time our waitress took a decent amount of time to get our food and drinks. We kept having to ask different waitresses that weren’t assigned to our table to bring us something we needed. One waitress in particular stood out to us, unfortunately I did not catch her name. She had short blonde/highlighted hair, and wore glasses. She was very attentive to us, despite not having us as her table. Her service was absolutely amazing, and she deserves to Be commended for it. Overall food was great, just need to decrease guest wait time.

I had the pleasure of DJing last Sunday at this Restaurant for Mr David Vann. Can you believe it? I've never been here before, and the first time I get to go, it's to work?
